text:
If they say, “Come with us,
Let’s lie in wait for blood,
Let’s ambush the innocent without cause;

Turn to my rebuke,
Behold, I will pour out my spirit on you;
I will make my words known to you.

Do not let kindness and truth leave you;
Bind them around your neck,
Write them on the tablet of your heart.

He taught me and said to me,
“Let your heart take hold of my words;
Keep my commandments and live;

Like a loving doe and a graceful mountain goat,
Let her breasts satisfy you at all times;
Be exhilarated always with her love.

When you walk, they will guide you;
When you sleep, they will watch over you;
And when you awake, they will talk to you.

Until an arrow pierces through his liver;
As a bird hurries to the snare,
So he does not know that it will cost him his life.

The fear of the Lord is to hate evil;
Pride, arrogance, the evil way,
And the perverted mouth, I hate.

When He set a boundary for the sea
So that the water would not violate His command,
When He marked out the foundations of the earth;

Then I was beside Him, as a master workman;
And I was His delight daily,
Rejoicing always before Him,

All the brothers of a poor person hate him;
How much more do his friends abandon him!
He pursues them with words, but they are gone.

Do you see a person skilled in his work?
He will stand before kings;
He will not stand before obscure people.

Do not look at wine when it is red,
When it sparkles in the cup,
When it goes down smoothly;

Know that wisdom is the same for your soul;
If you find it, then there will be a future,
And your hope will not be cut off.

Prepare your work outside,
And make it ready for yourself in the field;
Afterward, then, build your house.

And behold, it was completely overgrown with weeds;
Its surface was covered with weeds,
And its stone wall was broken down.

Do not go out hastily to argue your case;
Otherwise, what will you do in the end,
When your neighbor humiliates you?

Do not abandon your friend or your father’s friend,
And do not go to your brother’s house on the day of your disaster;
Better is a neighbor who is near than a brother far away.

Keep deception and lies far from me,
Give me neither poverty nor riches;
Feed me with the food that is my portion,

For the churning of milk produces butter,
And pressing the nose produces blood;
So the churning of anger produces strife.
